Defendant Darnell D Walker in court with Attorney Michael J Steinle.  Defendant Darnell D Walker in custody.  Grant Ian Huebner appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Tamika S. and Kenyatta C.  AS TO COUNT #1:   The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be TEN (10) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FIVE (5) years with credit for THREE HUNDRED SIXTY-SIX (366) days time served.  Defendant shall serve FIVE (5) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program;
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - No contact with the victim's family;
 - Restitution in the amount of $1,600 made payable to Latanya Sanders;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  The Defendant shall pay restitution, fine and mandatory costs and surcharges from prison funds, including wages and all other moneys, in an amount or percentage the Department (DOC) determines to be reasonable and as a condition fo extended supervision.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay the amounts will result in a civil judgment.

